main event: A civilian reported observing an unidentified object in the Washington, D.C. area on July 5, 1952.
interesting points: The observation was made using a time-exposure photograph taken on April 8, 1952,The photographer noted nothing moving in the sky during the exposure,The object could potentially be attributed to several explanations, including a balloon or an astronomical phenomenon,The report indicated that the image had a distinct density, suggesting some distortion,The Air Force concluded that the negative provided did not indicate the existence of any unusual aerial object.
